ExpiredDate=function(text, Expired){
    text<-paste(sep="",substr(text, 9, length(options$Series)),"W30")
    year=""
    month=""
    date=""
    first=substr(text,1,1)
    second=substr(text,2,2)
    if(first=="A"||first=="M"){month="01"}
    if(first=="B"||first=="N"){month="02"}
    if(first=="C"||first=="O"){month="03"}
    if(first=="D"||first=="P"){month="04"}
    if(first=="E"||first=="Q"){month="05"}
    if(first=="F"||first=="R"){month="06"}
    if(first=="G"||first=="S"){month="07"}
    if(first=="H"||first=="T"){month="08"}
    if(first=="I"||first=="U"){month="09"}
    if(first=="J"||first=="V"){month="10"}
    if(first=="K"||first=="W"){month="11"}
    if(first=="L"||first=="X"){month="12"}
    if(second=="0"){year="2020"}
    if(second=="1"){year="2021"}
    if(second=="2"){year="2022"}
    if(second=="3"){year="2023"}
    if(second=="4"){year="2024"}
    day=substr(text,4,5)
    d1<-paste(sep="-", year, month, day)
    return (d1)
}
Sub=function(text){
    d=""
    c=substr(text, 4, 4)
    t=substr(text, 5, 5)
    if(c=="A"||c=="M") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "F", t)}
    if(c=="B"||c=="N") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "G", t)}
    if(c=="C"||c=="O") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "H", t)}
    if(c=="D"||c=="P") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "J", t)}
    if(c=="E"||c=="Q") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "K", t)}
    if(c=="F"||c=="R") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "M", t)}
    if(c=="G"||c=="S") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "N", t)}
    if(c=="H"||c=="T") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "Q", t)}
    if(c=="I"||c=="U") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "U", t)}
    if(c=="J"||c=="V") {d=paste(sep="","HSI", "V", t)}

price_diff=function(vec){
        q <- c()
        for(i in 1:nrow(vec)){
            if (vec$Type[i]=="call"){
            q[i] <- vec$Strike[i] - vec$mean_price[i]
        }   else q[i] <- vec$Strike[i] - (vec$mean_price[i] * 0.95)
    }
        return(q)
}

skewness=function(vec){
        q<-c()
        for(i in 1:nrow(vec)){
            if(i%%2==1){
            q[i] <- abs(vec$Impliedvolatility[i]-vec$Impliedvolatility[i+1])
            q[i+1] <- q[i]
            }
        }
        return(q)
}

options <- options %>% group_by(Series) %>% mutate(mean_price=mean(OptionSettlementPrice))

call_options <- options[options$Type == 'call',]
put_options <- options[options$Type == 'put',]

call_options_min_diff <- call_options %>% group_by(Strike) %>% filter(price_diff == abs(min(price_diff)))
put_options_min_diff <- put_options %>% group_by(Strike) %>% filter(price_diff == abs(min(price_diff)))

new <- rbind(call_options_min_diff,put_options_min_diff)
new <- new[order(new$Strike),]
new <- new %>% group_by(Strike) %>% filter(n()!=1)

n=length(new$mean_price)
daily_return = log(new$mean_price[-1]/new$mean_price[-n])
daily_return_normalized = (daily_return-min(daily_return))/(max(daily_return)-min(daily_return))
t.test((skewness(new))/2,daily_return_normalized)

options<-options[order(options$Series),]
s<-unlist(lapply(options$Underlying, Sub))
options<-transform(options,Underlying=s)
options<-(options%>%
filter(!is.na(Underlying)))
options<-options[order(options$Series),]
options<-(options%>%
left_join(futures, by = c("Date","Underlying"))%>%
filter(!is.na(SettlementPrice))%>%
filter(!is.na(StrikePrice))%>%
filter(!is.na(OptionSettlementPrice)))
s<-unlist(lapply(options$Series, ExpiredDate))
options<-transform(options,EXP=as.Date(s))
options<-(options%>%
filter(!is.na(EXP)))
options<-rename(options, "FuturesSettlementPrice"=`SettlementPrice`)
# Underlying daily mean price
UP<-(options%>%
group_by(Date, Underlying)%>%
summarize(mean(OptionSettlementPrice))%>%
rename("SettlementPrice"=`mean(OptionSettlementPrice)`))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Date'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
#UP
# volatility spread 
options[which(options$Type=="put"),'Impliedvolatility'] <- (-1*options$Impliedvolatility[options$Type=="put"])
temp<-(options%>% 
group_by(Date, EXP, Underlying, StrikePrice, Type)%>%
summarize(mean(Impliedvolatility))%>%
rename("Impliedvolatility"=`mean(Impliedvolatility)`))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Date', 'EXP', 'Underlying', 'StrikePrice'.
## You can override using the `.groups` argument.
temp=as.data.frame(temp)
#head(n=200, temp)
VolatilitySpread<-(temp%>% 
group_by(Date, EXP, Underlying, StrikePrice)%>%
filter(n() == 2)%>%
summarize(sum(Impliedvolatility)))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Date', 'EXP', 'Underlying'. You can
## override using the `.groups` argument.
VolatilitySpread<-rename(VolatilitySpread, "VolatilitySpread"=`sum(Impliedvolatility)`)
#head(n=200, VolatilitySpread)
VolatilitySpread<-VolatilitySpread%>%
left_join(futures, by = c("Date","Underlying"))%>% 
filter(!is.na(SettlementPrice))
VolatilitySpread=as.data.frame(VolatilitySpread)
options[which(options$Type=="put"),'Impliedvolatility'] <- (-1*options$Impliedvolatility[options$Type=="put"])
#head(VolatilitySpread)
VolatilitySpread<-(VolatilitySpread%>%select(Date, Underlying, VolatilitySpread))
df = merge(VolatilitySpread, select(futures, 'Date', 'Underlying', 'SettlementPrice'), by=c("Date", "Underlying"), suffixes=c("_df1", "_df2"), all=TRUE)
colnames(df) = c('date', 'underlying', 'vs', 'price')
df = df %>%  
  filter(!is.na(date)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(underlying)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(price))

df$price = df$price/100
df$vs = df$vs/100
df$date = as.Date(df$date, "%Y-%m-%d")

# keep only underlying with time-series longer than 90 days
df_underlying_length = df %>% 
  group_by(underlying) %>% 
  count %>%
  filter(n > 90)
df = merge(df, select(df_underlying_length, 'underlying'), by=c("underlying"), suffixes=c("_df1", "_df2"))
df = df %>% mutate(vs_rank = findInterval(-vs, quantile(-vs, c(0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8, 1)), left.open = TRUE) + 1)

df = df %>%
  group_by(underlying) %>%
  mutate(price_5d_later = dplyr::lead(price, n = 5, default = NA)) %>%
  mutate(price_10d_later = dplyr::lead(price, n = 10, default = NA)) %>%
  mutate(price_30d_later = dplyr::lead(price, n = 30, default = NA)) %>%
  mutate(return_5d = log(price_5d_later/price)/5) %>%
  mutate(return_10d = log(price_10d_later/price)/10) %>%
  mutate(return_30d = log(price_30d_later/price)/30)

df = df %>%  
  filter(!is.na(return_5d)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(return_10d)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(return_30d))

#install.packages("TTR")
library(TTR)
df = df %>%
  mutate(vs_mean_5d = runMean(vs, 5)) %>%
  mutate(vs_mean_10d = runMean(vs, 10)) %>%
  mutate(vs_mean_30d = runMean(vs, 30)) %>%
  mutate(vs_sd_5d = runSD(vs, 5)) %>%
  mutate(vs_sd_10d = runSD(vs, 10)) %>%
  mutate(vs_sd_30d = runSD(vs, 30))
df = df %>%  
  filter(!is.na(vs_mean_5d)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs_mean_10d)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs_mean_30d)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs_sd_5d)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs_sd_10d)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs_sd_30d))

df = df %>%
  mutate(vs_5ma_factor = (vs - vs_mean_5d) / vs_sd_5d) %>%
  mutate(vs_10ma_factor = (vs - vs_mean_10d) / vs_sd_10d) %>%
  mutate(vs_30ma_factor = (vs - vs_mean_30d) / vs_sd_30d)
df = (df %>%  
  filter(!is.na(vs_5ma_factor)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs_10ma_factor)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(vs_30ma_factor)) %>%
  filter(!is.infinite(vs_5ma_factor)) %>%
  filter(!is.infinite(vs_10ma_factor)) %>%
  filter(!is.infinite(vs_30ma_factor)))

# logistic regression
df1 = select(df, 'return_10d', 'vs_rank')
## Adding missing grouping variables: `underlying`
df1$return_10d = (df1$return_10d > 0) * 1 # 上涨为1， 下降为0
model_lr = glm(formula = df1$return_10d ~ df1$vs_rank, family = "binomial", data = df1)

# ROC curve
library(ROCR)
prob_all = predict(object =model_lr,newdata=select(df1, 'vs_rank'),type = "response") 
## Adding missing grouping variables: `underlying`
pred = prediction(prob_all, df1$return_10d)
perf = performance(pred, 'tpr', 'fpr')
plot(perf, colorize=TRUE)
abline(0, 1, lty=3) # lty is the size of dot

  mutate(cross30 = (vs - vs_mean_30d) / vs_sd_30d) %>%
  mutate(cross30 = case_when(

  cross30 > 1.311 ~ 1,
  TRUE ~ 0))
